{
  "stem": "1799.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that was, in a way, quite a consolation, and it made it more palatable.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I belonged to the Maccabi Hatzair.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think they met like twice a week in the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, they met in the large common room we had in our house which was located in front of the synagogue, where the Jewish school lessons also took place.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Whenever there wasn't a school lesson, Maccabi Hatzair would meet there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was in, I think I was in-- 10, 11 years old, and preteen.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we learned about-- in those years we learned about Aliya.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We learned about Jews going to preparatory farms to learn how to harvest and work the land, which was, at that time, beginning to take place in Israel.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I personally was never attracted to it, having been influenced by my dad, who explained to me, and to the rest of the family, and to others, that he felt that that was not the solution.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was an old fashioned Jew, who did not believe that Israel was the answer to the future of Judaism.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is hard to make a statement of, but a lot of people felt that way at the time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They felt that the assimilation of Jews in countries was possible.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He had faith in that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a building directly in front of the synagogue, separated by a small courtyard to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had a two-story house.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was the size of a house with a basement, where I had lived and grew up from age 2 and 1/2 until age 13.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It had a formal dining room, and a formal sitting room or salon, and a kitchen.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
